 {"id":"coding_agent_usage_tracker-lw2","title":"Prompt: Add shell snippet generator and documentation","description":"## Summary
Provide ready-to-use shell snippets and a generator command for easy shell prompt integration.

## Background
Users should not have to figure out shell integration themselves. We provide:
1. A `caut prompt init <SHELL>` command that outputs ready-to-use snippets
2. Documentation for manual configuration
3. Support for bash, zsh, fish, and powershell

## Command Interface
```
caut prompt init <SHELL>

SHELLS:
    bash        Bash shell configuration
    zsh         Zsh shell configuration  
    fish        Fish shell configuration
    powershell  PowerShell configuration

OPTIONS:
    --right-prompt    Configure for right-side prompt (zsh/fish)
    --async           Use async prompt update (zsh)
    --minimal         Minimal configuration
```

## Generated Snippets

### Bash
```bash
# caut shell integration - add to ~/.bashrc
_caut_prompt() {
    local usage=$(caut prompt --cache-only 2>/dev/null)
    [ -n "$usage" ] && echo "[$usage] "
}
PS1='$(_caut_prompt)\u@\h:\w\$ '

# Optional: refresh cache after each command
PROMPT_COMMAND="${PROMPT_COMMAND:+$PROMPT_COMMAND ;} caut prompt --refresh &>/dev/null &"
```

### Zsh
```zsh
# caut shell integration - add to ~/.zshrc
autoload -Uz add-zsh-hook

_caut_prompt() {
    CAUT_PROMPT=$(caut prompt --cache-only 2>/dev/null)
}
add-zsh-hook precmd _caut_prompt

PROMPT='${CAUT_PROMPT:+[$CAUT_PROMPT] }%n@%m:%~%# '
```

### Fish
```fish
# caut shell integration - add to ~/.config/fish/config.fish
function _caut_prompt
    set -l usage (caut prompt --cache-only 2>/dev/null)
    test -n "$usage"; and echo "[$usage] "
end

function fish_prompt
    _caut_prompt
    echo (prompt_pwd) "> "
end
```

### PowerShell
```powershell
# caut shell integration - add to $PROFILE
function prompt {
    $usage = caut prompt --cache-only 2>$null
    if ($usage) { "[$usage] " }
    "PS $($executionContext.SessionState.Path.CurrentLocation)$('>' * ($nestedPromptLevel + 1)) "
}
```

## Implementation
