 {"id":"coding_agent_usage_tracker-moy","title":"Config: Provider-specific settings","description":"## Overview
Implement per-provider configuration for timeouts, enabling/disabling, priority ordering, and custom settings.

## Background & Rationale
Different providers have different characteristics:
- Claude CLI might be slow (needs longer timeout)
- User might want to disable Codex entirely
- Priority affects which provider is tried first in fallback scenarios
- Some providers might need custom settings (API endpoints, etc.)

## Technical Approach

### 1. Provider Config Structure
```rust
// In core/config.rs
#[derive(Debug, Deserialize, Default)]
#[serde(default)]
pub struct ProviderConfig {
    /// Whether this provider is enabled.
    pub enabled: bool,

    /// Priority for ordering (lower = higher priority).
    pub priority: Option<i32>,

    /// Override timeout for this provider specifically.
    pub timeout_seconds: Option<u64>,

    /// Override default strategies to try.
    pub strategies: Option<Vec<String>>,

    /// Custom API endpoint (for enterprise/proxy setups).
    pub api_base: Option<String>,
}
```

### 2. Example Config
```toml
[providers.claude]
enabled = true
priority = 1
timeout_seconds = 15
strategies = ["oauth", "cli-pty"]  # Skip web scraping

[providers.codex]
enabled = true
priority = 2
# Uses default timeout and strategies

[providers.gemini]
enabled = false  # Disabled entirely

[providers.cursor]
enabled = true
priority = 3
api_base = "https://internal-proxy.company.com/cursor"
```

### 3. Merging with Defaults
```rust
impl Config {
    /// Get effective config for a provider.
    pub fn provider_config(&self, provider: Provider) -> ProviderConfig {
        let name = provider.cli_name();

        self.providers
            .get(name)
            .cloned()
            .unwrap_or_else(|| ProviderConfig {
                enabled: true,  // Default: all providers enabled
                priority: Some(provider.default_priority()),
                timeout_seconds: None,
                strategies: None,
                api_base: None,
            })
    }
}

impl Provider {
    pub fn default_priority(&self) -> i32 {
        match self {
            Provider::Claude => 1,
            Provider::Codex => 2,
            Provider::Gemini => 3,
            Provider::Cursor => 4,
            Provider::Windsurf => 5,
        }
    }
}
```

### 4. Integration with Fetch Plan
```rust
// In core/fetch_plan.rs
impl FetchPlan {
    pub fn from_config(provider: Provider, config: &ProviderConfig) -> Self {
        let base_plan = match provider {
            Provider::Claude => claude::fetch_plan(),
            // ... etc
        };

        // Apply config overrides
        let mut plan = base_plan;

        if let Some(timeout) = config.timeout_seconds {
            plan.timeout = Duration::from_secs(timeout);
        }

        if let Some(strategies) = &config.strategies {
            plan.strategies.retain(|s| strategies.contains(&s.id.to_string()));
        }

        plan
    }
}
```

### 5. Filtering Enabled Providers
```rust
impl ResolvedConfig {
