 {"id":"coding_agent_usage_tracker-okl","title":"API: Implement daemon mode with process management","description":"## Summary
Run caut server as a background daemon with proper process management.

## CLI Flags
- `caut serve --daemon` - Fork to background
- `caut serve --pidfile /var/run/caut.pid` - Write PID file
- `caut serve stop` - Stop running daemon

## Implementation
```rust
pub fn daemonize(config: &ServerConfig) -> Result<()> {
    // Fork process
    match fork()? {
        ForkResult::Parent { child } => {
            // Write PID file
            if let Some(pidfile) = &config.pidfile {
                fs::write(pidfile, child.to_string())?;
            }
            println!("caut server started (PID: {})", child);
            std::process::exit(0);
        }
        ForkResult::Child => {
            // Become session leader
            setsid()?;

            // Redirect stdio to /dev/null
            redirect_stdio_to_null()?;

            // Run server
            run_server(config)
        }
    }
}
```

